parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair or replace Takata airbags can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbags may deploy incorrectly or not deploy at all.
symptoms: No symptoms are reported
as the issue is related to a recall notice and the potential for future failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a potential problem with the airbag system, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
indicating a potential problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger occupant detection system can lead to the airbag not deploying correctly in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger airbag may not deploy correctly in the event of an accident
or the system may not detect the presence of a passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump module can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the check engine warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle has low fuel pressure
the vehicle has difficulty starting or won't start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain tensioner can cause the engine to fail, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing accidents or loss of control while driving.
symptoms: The engine fails or locks up
the timing chain slips or breaks
the check engine warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle has difficulty starting or won't start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause engine problems, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or loss of control while driving.
symptoms: The intake manifold fails
the engine has difficulty running or won't start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator and oil leaks can cause engine overheating, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or loss of control while driving.
symptoms: The radiator leaks
the oil leaks
the engine overheats

the fuel pump leaks fuel
the fuel pump control module fails

the fuel pump control module fails
the engine fails to start
the check engine light illuminates

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall remedies for the fuel system can cause owners to experience delays in getting their vehicles repaired, which can increase the risk of accidents due to fuel pump failure.
symptoms: Owners receive recall notifications but are unable to get their vehicles repaired due to the unavailability of parts.
